result.execSummary:
The defendant Clifford D. Jamison Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Firearm-Convicted of a Felony, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Clifford D. Jamison in court with attorney Brian H. Wright.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court withholds sentence and places defendant on 1 yr. probation; condition: 5 days jail, credit for 4 days served.  Report start date to clerk before leaving today; waive costs.
